AV Project Engineer
- ,
Date Posted: 2014/04/29 04:45:28
Ref. JB3045242
Job Description
• AV infrastructure support, design, installation and commissioning including conference room control systems, video teleconference systems, scheduling systems, and digital projectors.
• Reading and understanding construction drawings and related documentation.
• Basic knowledge in Control system programming, and DSP configuration.
• Implementation of A/V systems.
• A/V systems installation support.
• Test and commissioning of A/V System.
• Plan and follow up projects.
• Provide implementation assistance, as well as testing and trouble shooting of the wiring loom with the technicians.
• Understand all of the devices to be and Check design drawings and offer suggestions and solutions to ease implementation.
• Train internal staff and Client members.
• Implement Company Quality Management System.
• Work Experience in Visio and AutoCAD.
• Basic Project management capabilities.
• Audio Visual Systems integration, design and installation.
• Support Sales in preliminary design proposal.
• Performed site surveys and installations of various audio, video and electronic systems.
• Responsible for overseeing completion of projects and managing additional techs on projects.
• Supervise field technicians based on system drawings and project requirements.
• Provide training material & project documentation of projects.
• Testing, commissioning, training and project handover.
• Troubleshoot and maintain AV system installations.
• Strong analytical and product management skills required, including a thorough understanding of how to interpret customer business needs and translate them into application and operational requirements.
• Project Management, Networking, Control System Programming.
• Ability to work independently and in a team environment.
• Excellent verbal and written communication skills and the ability to interact professionally with a diverse group.
• Excellent time management and organization skills and the ability to multi-task in a fast paced, large environment setting.
Skills
- CTS/CTS-I/CTS-D Certification will be added advantage.
- Familiarity with Clearone, Biamp, Tandberg, or Crestron Control Systems.
